# ── OS / Editor ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
~$*
*.swp
*.swo
.Rhistory
.RData
.Rproj.user/

# ── Build intermediates ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.html

# ── Journal-delivery bundle ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# manuscript/submission/ is the rebuildable delivery folder produced by
# analysis/render/builders/build_submission_bundle.sh. It's a snapshot
# of the rendered docx + supplementary-table xlsx files and gets
# clobbered on every render, so don't track it.
/manuscript/submission/

# ── R / knitr artifacts ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*_cache/
*_files/

# ── Claude / AI artifacts ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.claude/

# ── LSF job logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
logs/

# ── PHI / data ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default: ignore everything under data/. We then explicitly step into the
# subfolders that contain PHI-masked artifacts we *do* want tracked.
# (Can't use "data/**" here — git won't re-include files inside excluded dirs,
# so we ignore each level's children and whitelist the needed paths.)
/data/*
!/data/.gitkeep
!/data/raw/
!/data/flags/
!/data/processed/

# data/raw/: phi_safe xlsx committed, phi_unsafe xlsx never tracked
/data/raw/*
!/data/raw/.gitkeep
!/data/raw/phi_safe/
/data/raw/phi_safe/*
!/data/raw/phi_safe/*.xlsx
# Belt: phi_unsafe remains ignored even if a future rule tries to re-include it
/data/raw/phi_unsafe/

# data/flags/: masked audit-flag config committed
/data/flags/*
!/data/flags/*.csv
!/data/flags/*.md

# data/processed/: regenerated locally, never tracked. Historical
# variant_detection/ + spatial_tx/ mirrors were dropped 2026-05-05;
# manuscript producers now read upstream submodules directly via
# upstream_path() (see analysis/helper_scripts/utils.R + STRUCTURE.md
# rule R3). Single source of truth, never stale.
/data/processed/*

# ── Analysis outputs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Permissive flip 2026-05-11: track all PHI-safe results (figures, summary
# stats, etc.) so they're available on GitHub. Block only large Seurat/R
# binaries (handled by the *.rds / *.rda belt below) — those regenerate from
# upstream submodules.
!results/
!results/**

# ── Data file extensions (belt-and-suspenders) ───────────────────────────────
# Scope: only fire under data/. results/ tracks its own xlsx/csv/tsv freely
# after the 2026-05-11 permissive flip.
/data/**/*.xlsx
/data/**/*.xls
/data/**/*.csv
/data/**/*.tsv
/data/**/*.sav
/data/**/*.dta
/data/**/*.parquet
/data/**/*.feather
/data/**/*.sas7bdat
# Tracked metadata exception: PRISMA literature-search counts (no PHI)
!/data/raw/prisma_counts.csv

# Large R-binary blocklist — keep .rds/.rda out of git everywhere
*.rds
*.rda
*.RData

# ── Panel resolver output (regenerated by analysis/render/resolve_panels.R) ──
manuscript/submission_prep/sections/_resolved/
docs/submission/sections/_resolved/
docs/submission/.quarto/

# ── Parity audit artifacts (PHI-free; cross-host evidence for regen) ─────────
# Placed after the *.tsv belt-and-suspenders so the exception actually wins.
!results/stats/
!results/stats/_parity/
!results/stats/_parity/*parity*.tsv
!results/stats/_parity/minerva_parity_baseline.txt

# ── PHI-safe data exceptions (repeated to beat the *.xlsx/*.csv belt) ───────
# The step-in block above re-includes the subdirs, but the *.xlsx and *.csv
# belt rules then re-exclude the files. These final exceptions pin them back.
!/data/raw/phi_safe/*.xlsx
!/data/flags/*.csv
!/data/flags/*.md
# data/audit/: generated catalogue workbooks stay ignored (regenerated by
# export_sample_changes.R); track only the provenance README so the dir is
# self-documenting in the repo.
!/data/audit/
!/data/audit/README.md

# ── Ad-hoc / stray outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Default R plot device dumps at project root (R writes Rplots.pdf when a
# script calls plot() outside a managed device — happens during interactive
# debugging). Never wanted in version control.
/Rplots.pdf

# One-off intermediate exports for collaborators that sit at the repo root.
# Move into results/ if any of these become real build outputs.
/STUDY_NA_rows_for_andy.xlsx

# ── Transient review / exploration artefacts ────────────────────────────────
# results/_review/ and results/_exploration/ are aggregator and ad-hoc-
# experiment scratch dirs that re-generate per build. Tracking them
# multiplied repo size with no shipping value. Removed 2026-05-17 in
# the LFS migration pass; .gitignore policy here prevents re-adding.
results/_review/
results/_exploration/

# ── Public release hardening (overrides any whitelist above) ─────────────────
# Cohort / patient data is NEVER committed to this public repo. These dir-level
# ignores are authoritative: files under an ignored dir cannot be re-included.
/data/raw/phi_safe/
/data/raw/phi_unsafe/
/data/flags/
/data/processed/
/data/audit/
# Externally composed (Adobe) figure assets — not pipeline-regenerable; kept
# locally for the precision-medicine composer but not carried in the repo.
/manuscript/external_figures/*.png
/manuscript/external_figures/*.pdf
/manuscript/external_figures/*.svg

# ── Figure deliverable: commit only the clean results/figures/ tree ──────────
# The producer working dirs below are regenerated by run_all (step 2) and then
# organized into results/figures/ (step 5). Kept locally, not committed.
/results/Figure1/
/results/Figure2/
/results/Figure3/
/results/Figure4/
/results/ExtendedData/
/results/SupplementaryTables/
/results/Table1/

# Remove data/ and manuscript/ from the repo entirely (local-only; supplied on request)
/data/
/manuscript/
